Challenge Boards - Product Requirements Document
Version: 1.0 Date: November 7, 2025 Status: Initial Planning Document Type: Product Requirements Document (PRD)

Executive Summary
Challenge Boards is an internal organizational application designed to facilitate health and fitness challenges within a business environment. The platform enables administrators to create and manage step/activity challenges while allowing participants to compete individually or in teams by sharing their health data from Apple Health and Google Fit ecosystems.

1. Project Overview
1.1 Purpose
Create an engaging platform for workplace fitness challenges that:

Promotes employee health and wellness
Builds team camaraderie through friendly competition
Provides visibility into participation and progress
Supports flexible challenge formats and durations
1.2 Scope
Internal organizational use only (not public-facing)
Support for iOS (Apple Health) and Android (Google Fit) health data
Web-based administration and viewing
Companion mobile app for health data synchronization
Custom challenge creation and management
1.3 Success Criteria
Successfully track and display health metrics from multiple platforms
Enable smooth challenge signup and team formation process
Provide real-time leaderboards and progress tracking
80%+ employee participation in challenges
Minimal administrative overhead
2. User Roles & Personas
2.1 Admin/Manager
Responsibilities:

Create and configure challenges
Modify team assignments after signup period
Access all participant data and metrics
Generate reports and export data
Monitor challenge progress and engagement
User Stories:

As an admin, I want to create a new challenge with custom duration and rules
As an admin, I want to modify team rosters after the signup period closes
As an admin, I want to export challenge data to CSV for analysis
As an admin, I want to view real-time leaderboards across all challenges
2.2 Team Captain
Responsibilities:

Submit team name during challenge signup
Submit initial team roster during signup period
Rally team participation (informal)
User Stories:

As a team captain, I want to create a team and invite members during signup
As a team captain, I want to give my team a creative name
As a team captain, I want to see my team's progress during the challenge
2.3 Participant
Responsibilities:

Opt-in to share health data for challenges
Sync health data regularly
View personal and team progress
Engage with challenge activities
User Stories:

As a participant, I want to easily connect my Apple Health/Google Fit data
As a participant, I want to see my daily steps and how I rank
As a participant, I want to view my team's collective progress
As a participant, I want to choose whether my data remains visible after challenges end
3. Core Features & Functionality
3.1 Health Data Integration
Metrics Tracked:
Steps (primary metric)
Active Minutes (movement/exercise time)
Distance (miles/kilometers)
Data Sources:
Apple Health (iOS) - via HealthKit API
Google Fit (Android) - via Google Fit REST API
Data Sync Strategy:
Phase 1: Manual data entry via web interface
Phase 2: Automated sync via companion mobile app (.NET MAUI)
Daily background sync when mobile app is installed
On-demand sync button in mobile app
Data Privacy & Persistence:
Opt-in model: Users explicitly consent per challenge
All shared data persists indefinitely within the organization
Data visible to all participants during active challenges
Optional: Users can opt-in to ongoing visibility (Strava-style public record)
No external data sharing or public access
3.2 Challenge Management
Challenge Types:
Individual Competitions - Participants compete solo
Team Competitions - Teams compete for collective goals
Mixed Competitions - Multiple divisions/classes in same time period
Challenge Configuration:
Custom Duration - Admin defines start and end dates
Flexible Metrics - Choose which metrics count (steps, distance, active minutes)
Scoring Methods:
Total accumulation (sum of all values)
Daily average
Team average vs. team total (configurable)
Challenge Lifecycle:
Setup Phase - Admin creates challenge and opens signup
Signup Period - Team captains form teams, participants join
Active Phase - Data syncing and competition active
Completion Phase - Final results, winner announcement
Archive Phase - Historical data available for viewing
3.3 Team Management
Team Formation:
During Signup Period:

Team captain creates team
Captain submits team name
Captain adds initial roster
No team size limits (variable)
After Signup Period:

Only admin/manager can modify teams
Participants can be reassigned
Teams can be split or merged
Team Persistence:
Teams CAN persist across challenges (optional)
During signup, captain confirms team reuse or creates new
Historical team data always preserved
Team Scoring:
Configurable per challenge:
Sum of all member metrics
Average of all member metrics
Top N performers count
Minimum participation threshold
3.4 Dashboard & Visualization
Main Dashboard Features:
Active Challenges Overview

Current standings
Time remaining
Personal/team progress bars
Leaderboards

Individual rankings (with metrics)
Team rankings (with totals/averages)
Sortable by different metrics
Real-time updates
Progress Charts

Daily step trends (line charts)
Team comparison (bar charts)
Individual vs. team average
Historical performance
Personal Stats

Daily breakdown
Weekly summaries
Personal bests
Challenge participation history
Admin Dashboard:
Participation rates
Data sync status (who hasn't synced recently)
Challenge analytics
Engagement metrics
3.5 Notifications & Communication
Email Notifications:
Challenge invitation
Challenge start reminder
Daily/weekly progress updates
Milestone achievements
Final results announcement
Team Notifications (Future):
Stub API for future expansion
Support for team messaging
Challenge announcements
3.6 Reporting & Data Export
Built-in Reports:
Challenge summary report
Individual participant report
Team performance report
Participation and engagement report
Trend analysis across multiple challenges
Data Export:
Export to CSV on demand
Selectable date ranges
Include/exclude specific metrics
Raw data or aggregated summaries
4. Technical Architecture
4.1 Technology Stack
Backend:
Framework: ASP.NET Core Web API (.NET 8)
Language: C#
Authentication: Azure AD or custom JWT-based auth
API Style: RESTful
Database:
Primary: Azure SQL Database
User accounts and profiles
Challenge definitions
Team assignments
Health metrics (time-series data)
Cost Tier: Basic ($5/mo) to Standard ($15-50/mo)
Frontend:
Framework: React 18+ with TypeScript
UI Library: Material-UI or Tailwind CSS
Charts: Recharts or Chart.js
State Management: React Query + Context API
Hosting: Azure Static Web Apps or Azure App Service
Mobile App (Phase 2):
Framework: .NET MAUI (Multi-platform App UI)
Language: C#
Purpose: Health data sync only (minimal UI)
Platforms: iOS and Android
Native APIs:
iOS: HealthKit
Android: Google Fit API
Azure Services:
Azure App Service - Host Web API (Linux or Windows)
Azure SQL Database - Primary data store
Azure Functions - Background jobs (data processing, notifications)
Azure Blob Storage - Export files, backups
Azure Key Vault - API keys and secrets
Azure Application Insights - Monitoring and diagnostics
Azure Communication Services or SendGrid - Email delivery
