4.3 Database Schema (High-Level)
Core Tables:
Users - User profiles and authentication
Challenges - Challenge definitions and configuration
Teams - Team information and membership
TeamMembers - Many-to-many relationship
HealthMetrics - Time-series health data
ChallengeParticipants - Enrollment and consent
Leaderboards - Cached/computed rankings
AuditLog - Change tracking
4.4 Mobile App Strategy
Phase 1 (MVP):
Manual data entry via web app
Validates business logic before mobile investment
Phase 2 (Mobile Sync):
Simple companion app using .NET MAUI
Single button: "Sync Health Data"
Background daily sync
Minimal UI (not a full-featured app)
Distribution:
iOS: Apple Developer Program (Regular $99/year or Enterprise $299/year)
Android: Google Play ($25 one-time)
Recommendation: Enterprise program for internal-only distribution
5. User Flows
5.1 Challenge Creation Flow (Admin)
Admin navigates to "Create Challenge"
Enters challenge details:
Name and description
Start and end dates
Challenge type (individual/team/mixed)
Metrics to track (steps, distance, active minutes)
Scoring method
Configures team settings (if applicable)
Opens signup period
Notifies potential participants via email
5.2 Team Formation Flow (Captain)
Captain receives challenge invitation
Clicks "Create Team" during signup period
Enters team name
Searches and adds team members
Submits team roster
Team members receive notification to join
5.3 Participant Join Flow
Participant receives challenge invitation
Reviews challenge details
Opts in to data sharing consent
Chooses individual or joins team
(Phase 2) Downloads mobile app and connects health data
(Phase 1) Receives instructions for manual data entry
5.4 Daily Sync Flow (Mobile App)
Mobile app runs background sync (daily at set time)
App reads HealthKit/Google Fit data
Authenticates with API
POSTs new data to health metrics endpoint
Receives confirmation
Updates "Last Sync" timestamp in app
5.5 Leaderboard Viewing Flow
User logs into web app
Navigates to active challenge
Views real-time leaderboard
Filters by individual/team
Clicks on entry to see detailed breakdown
Views charts and trends
6. Non-Functional Requirements
6.1 Performance
Page load time < 2 seconds
API response time < 500ms (p95)
Leaderboard updates within 5 minutes of data sync
Support 100-500 concurrent users
6.2 Security
HTTPS only (TLS 1.2+)
JWT or Azure AD authentication
Role-based access control (RBAC)
API rate limiting
SQL injection prevention (parameterized queries)
Health data encryption at rest and in transit
Audit logging for sensitive operations
6.3 Scalability
Initial: 50-100 users
Growth: 500+ users
Database connection pooling
Redis caching for leaderboards (optional)
Azure scaling (vertical and horizontal)
6.4 Availability
99% uptime target
Azure health checks
Automated backups (daily)
Disaster recovery plan
6.5 Usability
Mobile-responsive web design
Accessible (WCAG 2.1 Level AA)
Intuitive navigation
Minimal clicks to key features
Clear error messages
6.6 Compliance
Internal organizational use (no HIPAA requirement)
Participants voluntarily share data
Clear consent mechanism
Data retention policy documented
Right to withdraw consent
7. Development Phases
Phase 1: MVP (Weeks 1-4)
Goal: Validate concept with manual data entry

Deliverables:

ASP.NET Core Web API (basic endpoints)
Azure SQL Database setup
React frontend with:
User authentication
Challenge creation (admin)
Team formation
Manual data entry form
Simple leaderboard
Email notifications (basic)
Deployed to Azure
Success Metrics:

Run one test challenge with team
Gather feedback on UX
Validate data model
Phase 2: Mobile Sync (Weeks 5-8)
Goal: Automate health data sync

Deliverables:

.NET MAUI companion app
HealthKit integration (iOS)
Google Fit integration (Android)
Background sync functionality
Enhanced API endpoints for bulk data ingestion
App deployment (TestFlight, Google Play Internal Testing)
Success Metrics:

90%+ successful sync rate
Daily automated updates
Reduced manual entry burden
Phase 3: Enhanced Features (Weeks 9-12)
Goal: Polish and engagement features

Deliverables:

Advanced charting and visualization
Admin dashboard with analytics
CSV export functionality
Multiple concurrent challenges
Achievement/milestone system
Improved notifications (summaries, digests)
Phase 4: Optimization (Weeks 13+)
Goal: Performance and scale

Deliverables:

Redis caching
Performance optimization
Enhanced reporting
Multi-tenant support (if needed)
Advanced team features
